pages.title: WELCOME TO JUNK JACK
pages.text:
Dig blocks, search for treasures,
build your humble shelter or huge castle,
fight monsters and find portals!

This guide will teach you the basics
of the game.

pages.title: DESTROYING BLOCKS
pages.text:
Almost everything can be
destroyed by interacting with it.
Punch some trees and start
gathering wood, useful to
craft basic items.

pages.title: GATHERING RESOURCES
pages.text:
Blocks drop useful resources, needed by
many craft recipes.
In the world you will find crates and
chests. They can contain treasures,
weapons, and much more!

pages.title: MOVING AROUND
pages.text:
Moving your character is easy.
Press the movement keys in the
direction you want to move.

For a quick help, press F1 while
playing to show all the keybindings.

pages.title: JUMPING
pages.text:
Press the jump button to jump on blocks.
Jump height can be boosted by
trinkets or armor pieces.

pages.title: BREAKING BLOCKS
pages.text:
Hold action button on a block to break it.
Blocks can be broken using appropriate 
tools, or bare hands.

pages.title: CLIMB LADDERS
pages.text: To climb a ladder just hold UP button on it.

pages.title: SWIMMING
pages.text:
To swim press the directonal keys to move
in your desidered direction.
Keep an eye on your oxigen level!

pages.title: INVENTORY
pages.text:
The inventory contains your backpack,
the crafting table - addons,
and the equip pane.

pages.title: CRAFTBOOK
pages.text:
The craftbook contains all 
available crafts and this guide.
If simple crafting is enabled the
craftbook is also used to craft items.

pages.title: MAP
pages.text:
The map shows an overview of the world.
You can zoom the map further back
by pressing interact button on the screen
while the map is open.

pages.title: QUICKSLOTS
pages.text:
Quickslots are used to hold items and
have quick access to them.
Just click a quickslot to select it.
Consume items by pressing the interact
button on a quickslot.

pages.title: CHAT
pages.text:
The chat button is available in multiplayer.
Use it to chat with other people!

pages.title: HOW TO CRAFT
pages.text:
Craft by dragging the
required items inside the
crafting grid.
More complex items
require an addon to be
crafted.

pages.title: FINDING NEW CRAFTS
pages.text:
During your adventure you will find
craft notes that contain new recipes,
useful for your adventure.
To add a note to the craftbook,
press the interact button on it.

pages.title: SIMPLE CRAFTING
pages.text:
Enable simple crafting in the options
to craft objects from the craftbook.
This way of crafting requires time
according to the craft difficulty.
Queue crafts by clicking multiple times.

pages.title: MANAGING INVENTORY
pages.text:
Managing inventory is simple.
Follow these simple steps to get
the best of it.

pages.title: MOVING ITEMS
pages.text:
To move an item, just drag it.
You can also first click on the item,
then click on a free slot to move it.

pages.title: CONSUMING ITEMS
pages.text:
Press the interact button on a usable item
like fruits or craft notes, to consume it.
If the item is in a quickslot,
press the interact button to consume it.

pages.title: MANAGING ITEMS
pages.text:
Use the interact button on a item to split
it in 2 piles.

Press shift+interact on a item to combine
all the similar items around it in the same slot.

pages.title: TRASHING ITEMS
pages.text:
Click on the trash to enable delete mode.
Select the items you want to trash and
confirm by clicking the trash button.

Delete a single item by dragging
it on the trash.

pages.title: ITEM CATEGORIES
pages.text:
Each item has its category shown
by a colored border in the inventory.
This option is disabled by default
and can be enabled through
the 'item outlines' option.

pages.title: THROW ITEMS
pages.text:
To throw an item, drag it out of the pane.
You can also throw items with the inventory
closed using the throw button.

pages.title: TOOL TYPES
pages.text:
Each tool has its own useful task:
^0Д^s> Shovels, useful to dig dirt.
^0Ё^s> Pickaxes, needed to destroy rocks.
^0Г^s> Axes, to chop trees.
^0Е^s> Work Hammers, used to break furniture,
   chests, and usable items.
^0Ж^s> Hoes, used for tilling soil when farming.

pages.title: BETTER TOOLS
pages.text:
Tools made of metal require
an Anvil addon to be crafted.
They break blocks faster,
and are more durable depending
on the metal quality.

pages.title: CRAFTING WITH THE ADDONS
pages.text:
Most crafts require an addon to be crafted.
Stand in front of the needed addon,
then press the interact button on it
or open the inventory.
The craft grid will show the relative addon.

pages.title: WEAPON TYPES
pages.text:
Weapons are used to fight monsters.
There are many different weapons,
each one with a particular type of damage.
Blunt, Slash, Pierce, Magic.
Different weapons also have different
speeds and knockback.

pages.title: MONSTER DEFENSES
pages.text:
Every monster can have weak or strong
defenses against specific damage
types. Try to find the most effective
weapon to kill them!

pages.title: BETTER WEAPONS
pages.text:
Weapons crafted with better
materials yield more damage,
and have a longer attack range.

pages.title: RANGED WEAPONS
pages.text:
Use ranged weapons from distance.
Click anywere in the screen to shoot.
Some ranged weapons require specific ammo.
Put ammo in the correct inventory
slot before using the weapon.

pages.title: EQUIP SLOTS
pages.text:
You can equip 5 different equip pieces:
hats/helms, chests, legs, feet and trinkets.
Click the equip label on the lower right of
the inventory to access your equip slots.

pages.title: EQUIP TYPES
pages.text:
There are many equippable items
that you can find and craft.
Some are just fancy items while
other give you benefits.

pages.title: EQUIP DAMAGES
pages.text:
There are 4 types of damages:
^0^s> slash damage
^0^s> blunt damage
^0^s> pierce damage
^0^s> magic damage

Every weapon, bullet and mob
has one specific type.

pages.title: EQUIP DEFENSES
pages.text:
There are 4 types of defenses:
^0^s> slash defense
^0^s> blunt defense
^0^s> pierce defense
^0^s> magic defense

Every armor, trinket and mob
has different values for each type.

pages.title: EQUIP RESISTANCES
pages.text:
There are 5 types of resistances:
^0^s> lava resistance
^0^s> acid resistance
^0^s> breath resistance
^0^s> explosion resistance
^0^s> fall damage resistance
Every armor and trinket has
different values for each type.

pages.title: EQUIP MOVEMENTS
pages.text:
There are 4 types of movement bonuses:
^0^s> walk speed
^0^s> climb speed
^0^s> dash speed
^0^s> swim speed

Every armor and trinket has
different values for each type.

pages.title: EQUIP BONUSES
pages.text:
Equip pieces can have diffent bonuses:
> attack bonuses increase damage
> defense bonuses reduce damage
  from mobs and bullets
> resistances reduce damage from special
  types of damage (up to 100% immunity)
> movement bonuses which increase
  movement speed

pages.title: SPECIAL BONUSES
pages.text:
There are many other stats:

^0^s> health (and healing) bonus
^0^s> luck
^0^s> spike damage
> light glow
> hidden bonuses!

pages.title: FANCY EQUIP
pages.text:
Click on the equip button twice to access
the fancy equip. Here you can dress different
equip pieces to show
while keeping the primary item stats.

pages.title: SURVIVE IN A HOSTILE WORLD
pages.text:
When night comes, monsters will spawn.
Build a shelter to protect yourself!
Gather coal from dirt, use it with
wood planks to craft some torches.
Remember: most monsters won't
spawn in well-lit areas!

pages.title: HOME SWEET HOME
pages.text:
Press the interact key on a bed to use it
as a new spawn point.
If you die you will respawn there.
Interact the bed at night to sleep, this makes
you skip the night and restores your health.

pages.title: HOW TO BUILD
pages.text:
To build, drag a placeable block or item
into a quickslot, select it, and click
where you want it to be placed.

pages.title: PLACING BLOCKS
pages.text:
1. Back layer is filled before the front one.
2. Place a block on yourself to
automatically jump over it!
Hold shift to place blocks only in one layer.

pages.title: PLACING DOORS AND OTHER ITEMS
pages.text:
Some items, like doors, require
to be attached to the block
below, above or behind.
If you see a red square you're
placing it in the wrong way!

pages.title: ORGANIZE YOUR STUFF
pages.text:
Chests help you store items
gathered in your adventures.
Metal chests hold more objects.
Stack chests and addons by
placing them on top of each other.

pages.title: GROW PLANTS
pages.text:
Grow wheat, fruit trees and
many other types of plants!
Eventually, fruits will grow on plants, click
them with bare hands to make them fall.
Seeds can be found in crates underground.

pages.title: TILLING GROUND AND SUPPORTS
pages.text:
Some plants require tilled soil,
that must be prepared with a hoe,
while others require specific supports.

pages.title: USE THE FORGE
pages.text:
Use the forge to smelt
ingots, craft glass,
or cook meat. Place fuel
into the right slot and
the item you want to
smelt or cook into the
left slot.

pages.title: FORGE FUEL
pages.text:
The forge will automatically work
as long as there is fuel and items to consume.

There are many fuel types, some
are more efficient than others.

pages.title: CAPTURE ANIMALS
pages.text:
Breeding is used to grow animals
in specific stable blocks.
Capture animals with the taming collar.
Interact on a animal with the collar selected
and you will capture it in your inventory.

pages.title: STABLE ANIMALS
pages.text:
To stable an animal, just place
it on the appropriate stable.
Each stable can hold up to 3 animals.

pages.title: STABLE INTERFACE
pages.text:
Interact a stable to see its content and the
status of the respective stabled animals.
The pane shows stabled animals,
their gender and happiness.

pages.title: FEEDING ANIMALS
pages.text:
Place food in the stable slot and your
animals will use it when they're hungry.
Different kinds of animals like different
kinds of foods.

pages.title: LOVE IS IN THE AIR
pages.text:
Well fed animals of the same stable will
breed a baby if there is room available.
Keep animals near their home stable,
or they will flee!

pages.title: MAKE A FRIEND
pages.text:
Captured mobs can follow you around!
Just place their item in the trinket slot
to summon them beside you.
There are even some secret companions,
try to find them!

pages.title: COOKING FOODS
pages.text:
Cook a variety of foods with
the cooking pot and cooking ware.
Some recipes will need one,
or even both of them.

Remember: Cooked food is more effective!

pages.title: TRAVEL TO OTHER DIMENSIONS
pages.text:
During your adventure you might find
special chests that contain portal pieces.
To build a portal you need 3 portal pieces.

Portal Chests only spawn in
adventure worlds.

pages.title: TRAVEL TO OTHER DIMENSIONS
pages.text:
Place three pieces in the shown
order and a portal will appear.
Interact with the portal to
travel to a new planet.

pages.title: JEWELCRAFTING
pages.text:
Jewelcraft allows you to encrust your tools,
weapons and armors with gems to imbue
them with useful powers.

pages.title: JEWELCRAFTING
pages.text:
Cut a gem with the
tinkerer's tools, then consume the gem
and choose what to encrust.

pages.title: JEWELCRAFTING
pages.text:
The encrusted item will show the gem icon
while in the inventory. Available powers are:
> Power, durability or uses enhancements.
> Attack or defense bonuses.
> Side effects, such as double drops.
> Light glows.
> Immunities.
> Secret powers!

pages.title: SIGNS
pages.text:
Interact on a sign to read its contents.
To edit a sign first craft a pencil,
then select it and interact with the
sign to open the edit view.

pages.title: TRADES
pages.text:
To trade with someone interact with him
while holding a Trading Scale.
Select the items you want to trade.
Accept the trade by clicking the button.
(Cancel the trade by clicking the backpack.)

pages.title: FURNITURE
pages.text:
Place a furniture frame, then place a liner
on top of it to combine them.
Paint your furniture to make it unique!

pages.title: CHEMISTRY
pages.text:
Chemistry allows you to create mixtures
by using the Chemistry Lab addon.

There are 4 kinds of potions: offensive,
defensive, utility and special potions.

Two effects of the same type
cannot stack!

pages.title: CHEMISTRY
pages.text:
To brew a potion:
1. place reagents in
top 3 slots.
2. place an empty bottle.
3. pofuse the craft button.

Not all combinations
create a useful mixture!

pages.title: CHEMISTRY
pages.text:
Varying the reagents alters the effect
and the strength of the potion.

Using better bottles enhances the duration
instead. Discover them all!

pages.title: FISHING
pages.text:
To fish, equip a fishing pole and place a
fishing lure in the ammo slot.
Click anywhere to cast the bobber and wait.
When the bobber moves down permanently
quickly click again to catch your prey!

pages.title: FISH TANKS
pages.text:
There are many differents fishes at
different depths, day times or planets.
There are many special fishes too!
Don't forget to place them in fish tanks
to see them swim!

pages.title: ELECTRONICS
pages.text:
Electronics allows the construction of
complex circuits which are able to interact
with the world.

You will need an ^vElectrician's Bench^s
 and ^vSilicium^s to create all the required items.

pages.title: KINDS OF DEVICES
pages.text:
There are 4 kinds of electronics pieces:
1. ^vWires^s, which trasport electrical signals.
2. ^vDevices^s, which convert inputs into outputs
   and have specific behaviors.
3. ^vInput Devices^s, which gather inputs
from the world.
4. ^vOutput Devices^s, which receives signals
to produce active effects.

pages.title: SIGNALS
pages.text:
An electrical signal can have 4 statuses:
1. ^cOFF^s, when there is no signal.
2. ^2HIGH^s when the signal has a high value.
3. ^dLOW^s when the signal has a low value.
4. ^uUNSTABLE^s, when the signal is both
    high and low, this is an error status.

pages.title: ANALOG SIGNALS
pages.text:
In addition a signal can carry an analog
value which is a number between 0 and 15.

This analog value is propagated and can be
manipulated as if it is a multiple wire.

As an example an analog value of 11
would be sent as in binary 1011.

pages.title: WIRES
pages.text:
^vWires^s carry signals around, they can
be placed only on rear blocks.

They can be insulated with a ^vWire Insulator^s
to prevent further connections with
other wires or devices.
They can be removed with a hammer.

pages.title: DEVICES
pages.text:
^vDevices^s must be placed on rear blocks.

Most of them can be rotated with
the spanner primary action.
Some of them can be configured with
the spanner secondary action.

pages.title: LOGIC GATES
pages.text:
^vLogic Gates^s are a kind of devices which turn
one or two signals into an output.

The ^vNOT Gate^s, for example, inverts a signal,
while the ^vAND Gate^s produces a ^2HIGH^s signal
only if both inputs are ^2HIGH^s.
Logic Gates applied on analog signals are
applied on every subcomponent of the signal.

pages.title: SIGNAL GENERATORS
pages.text:
Some devices, like the ^vClock^s or the
^vSource Device^s, produce signals with no input.

The clock is really special because it
generates an oscillating signal.

pages.title: ADC/DAC DEVICES
pages.text:
Two devices, the ^vADC^s and ^vDAC^s device, are
used to extract or set single components
of an analog signal.

This means that you will be able to turn
a 1001 signal into a 1101 or get the 2nd
composite value as a new output.

pages.title: INPUT DEVICES
pages.text:
^vInput Devices^s generate signals from
external inputs.

For example:
- a ^vLever^s that can be toggled.
- a ^vLight Sensor^s that generates  an analog
  signal according to the light value
  in a specific tile.

pages.title: OUTPUT DEVICES
pages.text:
^vOutput Devices^s receive signals to
actuate effects in the world.

For example:
- a ^vDoor^s will open when receiving a ^2HIGH^s
  signal.
- a ^vLight Bulb^s will switch on when receiving
  a ^2HIGH^s signal.

pages.title: FINAL WORDS
pages.text:
Mastering electronics will take time and
much experimenting with trial and error.

Many devices have special behaviors which
are described in the corresponding
craft page of the book.

Feel free to experiment!

pages.title: COMBINING SEEDS
pages.text:
Gardening lets you grow unique flowers
by combining their seeds.
Combine two seeds by holding on them
to get new plant types!

pages.title: FLOWER POTS
pages.text:
Craftable pots can be placed on shelves,
put flowers in them!
Some pots can also be painted.

pages.title: WELCOME TO JUNK JACK
pages.text:
Dig blocks, search for treasures,
build your humble shelter or huge castle,
fight monsters and find portals
which lead to new worlds!

This guide will teach you the basics
of the game.

pages.title: DESTROYING BLOCKS
pages.text:
Almost everything can be
destroyed by tapping on it.
Tap some trees and start
gathering wood, useful to
craft basic items.

pages.title: GATHERING RESOURCES
pages.text:
Blocks drop useful resources, needed by
many craft recipes.
In the world you will find crates and
chests. They can contain treasures,
weapons, and much more!

pages.title: MOVING AROUND
pages.text:
Moving your character is easy.
Just slide your finger in the
direction you want to move.

pages.title: JUMPING
pages.text:
When you are near the edge
of a block you can do a dash
jump by swiping diagonally,
up or down.

pages.title: BREAKING BLOCKS
pages.text:
Tap blocks repeatedly to break them.
Enable the 'hold to break' option
in the main menu to break blocks
by holding your finger on them.

pages.title: CLIMB LADDERS
pages.text:
To climb ladders, just swipe up or down.
You can dash jump from ladder edges.

pages.title: SWIMMING
pages.text:
Swimming is allowed in blocks full of liquid.
To swim, swipe in the desired direction.
Keep breath under control and remember
that some liquids hurt you!

pages.title: INVENTORY
pages.text:
The inventory contains your backpack,
the crafting table - addons,
and the equip pane.

pages.title: CRAFTBOOK
pages.text:
The craftbook contains all 
available crafts and this guide.
If simple crafting is enabled the
craftbook is also used to craft items.

pages.title: MAP
pages.text:
The map shows an overview of the world.
You can zoom the map further back
by holding your finger on the screen when
it is opened.

pages.title: QUICKSLOTS
pages.text:
You have some slots
to the right of the screen.
These are called 'quickslots'
and are used to hold items and
have quick access to them.
Just tap a quickslot to select it.

pages.title: CHAT
pages.text:
The chat button is only
available in multiplayer.
Use it to chat with other people!

pages.title: HOW TO CRAFT
pages.text:
Craft by dragging the
required items inside the
crafting grid. More
complex items require
an addon to be crafted.

pages.title: FINDING NEW CRAFTS
pages.text:
During your adventure you will find
craft notes that contain new recipes,
useful for your adventure.
To add a note to the craftbook,
hold your finger on it.

pages.title: SIMPLE CRAFTING
pages.text:
Enable simple crafting in the options
to craft objects from the craftbook.
This way of crafting requires time
according to the craft difficulty.
Queue crafts by tapping more times.

pages.title: MANAGING INVENTORY
pages.text:
Managing inventory is simple.
Follow these simple steps to get
the best of it.

pages.title: MOVING ITEMS
pages.text: To move an item, just drag it.

pages.title: CONSUMING ITEMS
pages.text:
Hold a finger on a usable item,
like fruits or craft notes, to consume it.
If the item is in a quickslot, you can
even tap to consume it.

pages.title: MANAGING ITEMS
pages.text:
Tap a selected item to split it in two even
piles. Hold your finger on an item to
combine all the similar items around
it in the same slot.

pages.title: TRASHING ITEMS
pages.text:
Tap the trash to enable item trashing.
Select the items you want to trash and
confirm by tapping the trash button.
Delete a single item by dragging
it on the trash.

pages.title: ITEM CATEGORIES
pages.text:
Each item has its category shown
by a colored border in the inventory.
This option is disabled by default
and can be enabled through
the 'item outlines' option.

pages.title: THROW ITEMS
pages.text:
To throw an item away, drag it
out of the pane. You can also throw items
with the inventory closed by holding your
finger on the screen where
you want to throw it.

pages.title: TOOL TYPES
pages.text:

^0Ё^s> Pickaxes, needed to destroy rocks.

pages.title: CRAFTING WITH THE ADDONS
pages.text:
Most crafts require an addon to be crafted.
Stand in front of the needed addon,
then tap it, or open the inventory.
The craft grid will be correctly themed
according to the addon you are using.

Remember that you need to have clear
path to a mob to attack it.

pages.title: RANGED WEAPONS
pages.text:

Tap the screen to shoot! Some ranged
weapons require specific ammo, like the bow.
Put ammo in the correct inventory
slot before using the weapon.

that must be prepared with a hoe,
while others require specific supports.

pages.title: HOW TO USE THE FORGE
pages.text:
Use the forge to smelt
ingots, craft glass,
or cook meat. Place fuel
into the right slot and
the item you want to
smelt or cook into the
left slot.

pages.title: FORGE FUEL
pages.text:
The forge will automatically work
as long as there is fuel and items
to consume.
There are many fuel types, some
are more efficient than others.

pages.title: CAPTURE ANIMALS
pages.text:
Breeding is used to grow animals
in specific stable blocks.
Capture animals with the taming collar.
Tap on the animal with the collar selected,
and you will capture it in your inventory.

pages.title: STABLE ANIMALS
pages.text:
To stable an animal, just place
it on the appropriate stable.
Each stable can hold up to 3 animals.

pages.title: STABLE INTERFACE
pages.text:
Tap a stable to see its content and the
status of the respective stabled animals.
The pane shows stabled animals,
their gender and happiness.

pages.title: FEEDING ANIMALS
pages.text:
Place food in the stable slot and your
animals will use it when they're hungry.
Different kinds of animals like different
kinds of foods.

pages.title: LOVE IS IN THE AIR
pages.text:
Well fed animals of the same stable will
breed a baby if there is room available.
Keep animals near their home stable,
or they will flee!

pages.title: MAKE A FRIEND
pages.text:
Captured mobs can follow you around!
Just place their item in the trinket slot
to summon them beside you.
There are even some secret companions,
try to find them!

pages.title: COOKING FOODS
pages.text:
Cook a variety of foods with
the cooking pot and cooking ware.
Some recipes will need one,
or even both of them.
Remember: Cooked food is more effective!

pages.title: TRAVEL TO OTHER DIMENSIONS
pages.text:
During your adventure you might find
special chests that contain portal pieces.
To build a portal you need 3 portal pieces.
REMEMBER: Portal Chests only spawn in
adventure worlds.

pages.title: TRAVEL TO OTHER DIMENSIONS
pages.text:
Place three pieces in the shown
order and a portal will appear.
2. Tap the portal to travel to a new planet.

pages.title: JEWELCRAFTING
pages.text:
Jewelcraft allows you to encrust your tools,
weapons and armors with gems to imbue
them with useful powers.

pages.title: JEWELCRAFTING
pages.text:
First, you need to cut a gem with the
tinkerer's tools, then consume the gem
and choose what to encrust.

pages.title: JEWELCRAFTING
pages.text:
The encrusted item will show the gem icon
while in the inventory. Available powers are:
> Power, durability or uses enhancements.
> Attack or defense bonuses.
> Side effects, such as double drops.
> Light glows.
> Immunities.
> Secret powers!

pages.title: SIGNS
pages.text:
Tap a sign to read its contents.
To edit a sign first craft a pencil,
then select it and tap the
sign to open the edit view.

pages.title: TRADES
pages.text:
To trade with someone tap him while
holding a Trading Scale.
Tap the items you want to trade.
Accept the trade by tapping the button.
(Cancel the trade by tapping the backpack.)

pages.title: FURNITURE
pages.text:
Place a furniture frame.
Place a liner on top of it to combine them.
Paint your furniture to make it unique!

pages.title: CHEMISTRY
pages.text:
Chemistry allows you to create mixtures
by using the Chemistry Lab addon.

There are 4 kinds of potions: offensive,
defensive, utility and special potions.

Two effects of the same type
cannot stack!

pages.title: CHEMISTRY
pages.text:
To brew a potion:
place reagents in
top 3 slots.
place an empty bottle.
use the craft button.

Not all combinations
create a useful mixture!

pages.title: CHEMISTRY
pages.text:
Varying the reagents alters the effect
and the strength of the potion.

Using better bottles enhances the duration
instead. Discover them all!

pages.title: FISHING
pages.text:
To fish, equip a fishing pole and place a
fishing lure in the ammo slot.
Tap anywhere to cast the bobber and wait.
When the bobber moves down permanently
quickly tap the screen to catch your prey!

pages.title: FISH TANKS
pages.text:
There are many differents fishes at
different depths, day times or planets.
There are many special fishes too!
Don't forget to place them in fish tanks
to see them swim!

pages.title: ELECTRONICS
pages.text:
Electronics allows the construction of
complex circuits which are able to interact
with the world.

You will need an ^vElectrician's Bench^s
 and ^vSilicium^s to create all the required items.

pages.title: KINDS OF DEVICES
pages.text:
There are 4 kinds of electronics pieces:
1. ^vWires^s, which trasport electrical signals.
2. ^vDevices^s, which convert inputs into outputs
   and have specific behaviors.
3. ^vInput Devices^s, which gather inputs
from the world.
4. ^vOutput Devices^s, which receives signals
to produce active effects.

pages.title: SIGNALS
pages.text:
An electrical signal can have 4 statuses:
1. ^cOFF^s, when there is no signal.
2. ^2HIGH^s when the signal has a high value.
3. ^dLOW^s when the signal has a low value.
4. ^uUNSTABLE^s, when the signal is both
    high and low, this is an error status.

pages.title: ANALOG SIGNALS
pages.text:
In addition a signal can carry an analog
value which is a number between 0 and 15.

This analog value is propagated and can be
manipulated as if it is a multiple wire.

As an example an analog value of 11
would be sent as in binary 1011.

pages.title: WIRES
pages.text:
^vWires^s carry signals around, they can
be placed only on rear blocks.

They can be insulated with a ^vWire Insulator^s
to prevent further connections with
other wires or devices.
They can be removed with a hammer.

pages.title: DEVICES
pages.text:
^vDevices^s must be placed on rear blocks.

Most of them can be rotated with
the spanner primary action.
Some of them can be configured with
the spanner secondary action.

pages.title: LOGIC GATES
pages.text:
^vLogic Gates^s are a kind of devices which turn
one or two signals into an output.

The ^vNOT Gate^s, for example, inverts a signal,
while the ^vAND Gate^s produces a ^2HIGH^s signal
only if both inputs are ^2HIGH^s.
Logic Gates applied on analog signals are
applied on every subcomponent of the signal.

pages.title: SIGNAL GENERATORS
pages.text:
Some devices, like the ^vClock^s or the
^vSource Device^s, produce signals with no input.

The clock is really special because it
generates an oscillating signal.

pages.title: ADC/DAC DEVICES
pages.text:
Two devices, the ^vADC^s and ^vDAC^s device, are
used to extract or set single components
of an analog signal.

This means that you will be able to turn
a 1001 signal into a 1101 or get the 2nd
composite value as a new output.

pages.title: INPUT DEVICES
pages.text:
^vInput Devices^s generate signals from
external inputs.

For example:
- a ^vLever^s that can be toggled.
- a ^vLight Sensor^s that generates  an analog
  signal according to the light value
  in a specific tile.

pages.title: OUTPUT DEVICES
pages.text:
^vOutput Devices^s receive signals to
actuate effects in the world.

For example:
- a ^vDoor^s will open when receiving a ^2HIGH^s
  signal.
- a ^vLight Bulb^s will switch on when receiving
  a ^2HIGH^s signal.

pages.title: FINAL WORDS
pages.text:
Mastering electronics will take time and
much experimenting with trial and error.

Many devices have special behaviors which
are described in the corresponding
craft page of the book.

Feel free to experiment!

pages.title: COMBINING SEEDS
pages.text:
Gardening lets you grow unique flowers
by combining their seeds.
Combine two seeds by holding on them
to get new plant types!

pages.title: FLOWER POTS
pages.text:
Craftable pots can be placed on shelves,
put flowers in them!
Some pots can also be painted.

Each category contains different kinds of crafts. Start with bare hands crafts for basic recipes.
These crafts are always available with no addon. These include basic wood tools and items.
Forge is a special addon that uses fuel to produce items over time.
Chemistry Lab is a special addon used to mix reagents into potions.
The workbench is used to craft all other addons and most of the interactive blocks like chests or ladders.
The anvil is used to craft all metal objects that don't require precise construction.
Tinkerer's tools are used to craft all small pieces and elements which require precise construction.
The woodworker bench is used to craft simple wood items, parts and blocks.
The carpentry bench is used to craft all complex furniture sets.
The mason bench is used to craft special blocks made of stone or other materials like gem blocks.
The spinning wheel is used to turn cloth and yarn into useful items like clothes or decorative elements.
The loom is used to turn raw textile materials into more useful yarn or cloth.
The dying machine is used to dye cloth items or make dyes from raw ingredients.
Tanning tools are used to cure leather and to craft leather objects like armor.
Cooking ware is used to prepare most basic cooking mixtures and ingredients.
Cooking pot is used to cook recipes.
The electrician's bench is used to produce all electrical and electronics devices.
